news.title: Berlin to buy 15,000 flats for $2.90 billion from Vonovia & Deutsche Wohnen
news.para: The acquisition comes nine days before elections in the German capital, where housing shortages and rapidly rising prices have become a hot issue. An advisory referendum on expropriating the two housing companies is due to be held in parallel with the city election.

news.title: China's nightmare Evergrande scenario is an uncontrolled crash
news.para: Evergrande’s main banks were told by China’s housing ministry this week that the developer won’t be able to make interest payments due Sept. 20, according to people familiar with the matter.

news.title: International investors brace for a great fall in China
news.para: China Evergrande's woes have been snowballing since May. Dwindling resources set against 2 trillion yuan ($305 billion) of liabilities have wiped nearly 80% off its stock and bond prices and an $80 million bond coupon payment now looms next week.

news.title: Amundi says it has $25 million exposure in China Evergrande Group
news.para: EMAXX data, which provides details of funds' holdings based on their latest public disclosures, shows Amundi held around $300 million worth of Evergrande's international market bonds back in March, making it the biggest overall holder at that time.

news.title: At unfinished Evergrande apartments in central China, buyers seek answers
news.para: The complex is among a host of uncompleted homes across the country that have seen work grind to a standstill as result of the crisis engulfing China Evergrande Group

news.title: Kerala CM says Rs 2,450 crore to be spent to rehabilitate families in coastal areas
news.para: ​​Vijayan said the 'Punargeham project' was part of the government's Life Mission initiative to ensure no one is left without an abode in the state.

news.title: Indiabulls Housing Finance raises $165 million via offshore papers
news.para: The bonds are supposed to be listed on the Singapore Stock Exchange and marked as high-yield securities, below the investment grade.

news.title: Court issues notice to ED on Avantha Group promoter's bail plea
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate last month had arrested Avantha Group promoter Gautam Thapar in a money laundering case following searches at multiple locations in Delhi and Mumbai.

news.title: REITs, InvITs inclusion in Nifty indices put on hold, says NSE
news.para: The exchange on August 23 had announced new eligibility criteria which allowed REITs and InvITs to be included in Nifty indices from September 30.

news.title: Goa: GIDC puts up 31 industrial plots from Verna 'SEZ land' for e-auction
news.para: GIDC is offering the industrial plots, which range from 1,506 sqm to 45,000 sqm, on long-term lease with the initial period being for 30 years. The base rate for the plots has been fixed at Rs 5,000 per sqm and the plots will be allotted to the highest bidder through a two-step process.

news.title: Thrissur: Consumer forum directs Vasthu Suktha Builders to pay compensation
news.para: The family members EPN Nair and his wife Sarala N Nair had entered into an agreement with the builders to purchase a flat in a residential complex at Athani on May 30, 2008.

news.title: Hubballi Dharwad civic body gets approval to auction open sites
news.para: HDMC is planning to issue a notification pertaining to auctioning in a couple of days for sale of 167 sites with different dimensions in the twin cities. The base value of the sites will be Rs 27 crore.

news.title: About 891 properties sold outside owner's family from 2016 to 2019: Chandigarh admin report
news.para: The report stated, “Between August 28, 2016, and December 31, 2019, a total of 891 residential properties in sectors 4 to 46 were sold on 50%, 30% and 20% basis to those outside the family of the original owner or shareholder. Out of 891 properties, the team carried out physical verification at 281.”

news.title: Tax payers' body moves Andhra Pradesh HC against property tax system
news.para: Sunkara Rajendra Prasad, the counsel for the tax paying body, said capital value is released only when someone sells his or her property.

news.title: Acted against 588 buildings in municipalities: Gujarat government to HC
news.para: In an affidavit, the urban development urban housing department said it will place details of buildings in municipal corporation areas with regard to fire NOCs after the corporations send them the data. It placed details with regard to enforcement of fire safety rules in municipalities.
